    "comment": "Rationale: Characterisation of GluR2 subunit in out-side out patches of oocytes overexpressing GluR2.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P19491] SyNGO ID 1194 (PMID:28057533, EM)\n[P19491] SyNGO ID 1206 (PMID:15610164, EM). Experimental description: The rat wild-type GluR2 flip and GluR2 flop cDNAs were kind gifts from Drs. Jim Boulter, Stephan F. Heinemann, and Michael Hollmann (Salk Institute, La Jolla, CA)",
